BACKGROUND OF THE INVENTION
1. Field of the Invention
This invention relates to illumination control systems and, in particular, projection display systems using illumination amplifiers.
2. Description of the Prior Art
Control of illumination has been accomplished in the prior art with mechanical devices. The well known aperture and shutter of a camera are common mechanical devices for controlling light. Other prior art illumination control arrangements are described hereafter.
In the photoplotter field, a photohead is used to control light for exposing film. Mechanically positioned filters and shutters are used for illumination control such as described in U.S. Pat. No. 3,330,182 issued in July 1967.
The prior art is represented in the art of record herein.
The prior art and subsequent art in illumination control is further defined in the art-of-record of the parent application Ser. No. 366,714 including U.S. Pat. No. 3,790,901 to White et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,778,791 to Lewicki et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,764,213 to O'Meara; U.S. Pat. No. 3,744,906 to Sato et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,720,923 to Chen et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,713,042 to Kinsel; U.S. Pat. No. 3,705,758 to Haskal; U.S. Pat. No. 3,696,344 to Feinleib et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,670,202 to Paine et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,558,892 to Seeley; U.S. Pat. No. 3,473,084 to Dodge; and U.S. Pat. No. 3,427,458 to Parfomak et al and in the art-of-record of the parent application Ser. No. 730,756 including U.S. Pat. No. 3,981,002 to Gardner; U.S. Pat. No. 3,798,452 to Spitz et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,786,486 to Torresi; U.S. Pat. No. 3,707,323 to Kessler et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,702,723 to Borden Jr.; U.S. Pat. No. 3,700,805 to Hanlon; U.S. Pat. No. 3,666,881 to Stein; U.S. Pat. No. 3,647,959 to Schlesinger et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,641,264 to Macovski; U.S. Pat. No. 3,627,408 to Fergason; U.S. Pat. No. 3,605,594 to Gerritsen; U.S. Pat. No. 3,576,364 to Zanoni; U.S. Pat. No. 3,566,021 to Jakes Jr.; U.S. Pat. No. 3,544,711 to De Bitetto; U.S. Pat. No. 3,541,254 to Orthuber; U.S. Pat. No. 3,527,879 to Pritchard; U.S. Pat. No. 3,444,316 to Gerritsen; U.S. Pat. No. 3,231,746 to Goodrich; and U.S. Pat. No. 2,169,838 to Herbst which are herein incorporated-by-reference. The prior art in illumination control is still further defined in the art-of-record of the referenced related applications including U.S. Pat. No. 3,836,916 to Wiley; U.S. Pat. No. 3,721,164 to Kuttigen; U.S. Pat. No. 3,703,858 to Canfora; U.S. Pat. No. 3,695,154 to Webster; U.S. Pat. No. 3,686,675 to Faul; U.S. Pat. No. 3,648,578 to Ritchie; U.S. Pat. No. 3,610,119 to Gerber; U.S. Pat. No.  3,595,147 to Blattner; U.S. Pat. No. 3,565,524 to Pabst et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,498,711 to Ables et al; U.S. Pat. No. 3,458,253 to Hansen; U.S. Pat. N